Class GroupedSeries<K,V>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Data, DataListener, DataMap<K,SeriesView<V>>, View

    public class GroupedSeries<K,V>
extends CalcMap<K,SeriesView<V>,DataSeries<V>>

    Create a view of a DataSeries containing the values in the DataSeries collected into groups.

    If no key function is provided then groups are formed by placing all values for which v1.equals(v2) into the same group (and values where !v1.equals(v2) into different groups). The key for each group is a value such that key.equals(v) for all values in the group.

    If a key function is provided then a key is generated for each value in the series, and groups formed such that the keys for all values in a group satisfy k1.equals(k2).

    The values in the groups appear in the same order as their order in the series.

    The series returned by get(Object) and CalcMap.values() will be emptied (set to length 0) if the group size becomes zero (and calls to get(Object) for groups that do not yet exist will create empty series, but not add them to the list of groups returned by CalcMap.values() ). If the group size subsequently becomes non-zero this same series will be reused. This allows external observers to monitor the size of a group (even before it has existed in the input series).

    Author:
    O. J. Coleman
